<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-614-688  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 614 688.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC User  June 6 1990 n134 p21(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EMAP Business andamp; Computer Publications(England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Unix portable first for Sony. (Sony introduces Laptop NEWSportable Unix workstation) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Sony Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Sony Laptop NEWS (Portable computer) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionPortable ComputersWorkstationsUNIX.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Unix portable first for Sony Sony has pulled a punch ahead of Toshiba withthe release of a portable Unix workstation which it claims will be the firstto market in the UK.andM;The Sony Laptop NEWS is a 20lb mains-powered Unix-based portable based on theSony NWS-1500 Series machines.andP;  Rather than offering new technology, theportable features a high level of component integration to deliver what theJapanese company maintains is &quot;the smallest Unix workstation in the market&quot;.andM;Steve Boniwell, Sony marketing manager, believes the portable extendsdistributed computing beyond the office environment.andP;  &quot;I'm not looking forvast volumes in 1990, but I believe that this machine brings Unixworkstations down to commodity level,&quot; he said.andM;In addition to mobility, Sony claims that the Laptop NEWS deliverscompetitive price/performance.andP;  The portable is built around a 25MHz MC68030processor, delivers 3.9mips, and is expected to cost around 8,500 pounds whenit ships in September.andP;  Toshiba, which has recently launched its $13,200SPARC-based SPARC LT portable workstation in Japan, has yet to confirm a UKrelease (see news, page 24).andM;Sony's offering comes with a 1120x780 mono LCD display, a 240Mb hard drive, 31/2-inch floppy disk drive and 8Mb RAM as standard.andP;  Standard softwareincludes X.Window System Version 11 and TCP/IP and XNS communications.andO;</TEXT></DOC>